courses.description: 3 Credits (3 Lectures) Introductory or beginning literacy level of basic math, reading, science, social studies and writing skills. Satisfactory/unsatisfactory grading only. Prerequisite: Pre-test to determine existing skill level and to evaluate deficiencies and determine specific needs.

3 Credits (3 Lectures) Beginning level of basic math, reading, science, social studies and writing skills. Satisfactory/unsatisfactory grading only. Prerequisite: ABE080 or pre-test to determine existing skill level and to evaluate deficiencies and determine specific needs.

3 Credits (3 Lectures) Low intermediate level of basic math, reading, science, social studies and writing skills. Satisfactory/ unsatisfactory grading only. Prerequisite: ABE081 or pre-test to determine existing skill level and to evaluate deficiencies and determine specific needs.

3 Credits (3 Lectures) High intermediate level of basic math, reading, science, social studies and writing skills. Satisfactory/ unsatisfactory grading only. Prerequisite: ABE082 or pre-test to determine existing skill level and to evaluate deficiencies and determine specific needs.
3 Credits (3 Lectures) The concepts of accounting for a personal service enterprise or small retail business. Prerequisite: RDG091. Approved for Tech Prep.

3 Credits (3 Lectures) Theory, rules, and procedures used in preparing federal income tax returns for individuals, corporations, and partnerships both manually and with the use of computer software. Prerequisite: RDG094.
3 Credits (3 Lectures) Theory and practice of accounting applicable to the accumulation, external reporting, and uses of financial information. Prerequisite: RDG094.
3 Credits (3 Lectures) Selection and analysis of accounting information for internal organization use by management. Prerequisite: ACC201.

3 Credits (3 Lectures) Functions and practical operation of payroll accounting, with examination of current payroll tax laws, methods of computing wages and salaries, timekeeping methods, and microcomputer software for payroll systems. Prerequisite: ACC100 or ACC201.

3 Credits (3 Lectures) Practical application of accounting utilizing QuickBooks Pro. Topics covered will include the general ledger, accounts receivable, accounts payable, job costing, and payroll. Prerequisite: ACC100 or ACC201.
